1.4.1 The variables can be considered to monitor the flow of visitor traffic to the site. Pageviews is the number of visitors to the site, and some of these will click on the page. From those that click on the site some will enrol, and some of those that enrol will continue to pay for the service. Make a suitable plot to examine the flow of traffic, so that you can compare the flow between the two groups.

The flow gets significantly reduced when moving from one part to another.

1.4.2 Check what you learn about the difference in flow of traffic between control and experiment using a lineup plot.
